{
  "image": "6590\\6590.jpg",
  "title": "The Muxe in the Snow",
  "description": "A renowned contemporary artist couldn’t buy an Indigenous person for his new piece of art - so he hires one instead: A third-gender Muxe who performs six different scenes that make no sense whatsoever. Six scenes and no plot? Call it avant-garde if I’m white. Call it trauma porn if I’m migrant, non binary and Indigenous.",
  "credits": "<strong>Cast</strong>: Reyna Álvarez, Braiden Janes<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Lighting: Payal Jotania, Sound: Mihaela Vasileva, Video: Erin Gruber<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Amy Dass<br/>",
  "website": "https://https://facebook.com/zapotecaqueen",
  "plain_language": "A famous artist hires an Indigenous person for his new art piece, because he couldn’t just buy one. A Muxe (a third-gender person from southern Mexico) performs six scenes that don’t follow a coherent or a clear story. It explores the tension between telling someone’s story and taking it over.",
